Step 1: User drops waste into the bin or scans using app.
Step 2: System reads input or AI model identifies type of waste.
Step 3: If biodegradable → send to compartment A
        If recyclable → send to compartment B
        If non-biodegradable → send to compartment C
Step 4: Measure bin level using sensors.
Step 5: If bin level ≥ 90% → send alert to waste collection authority.
Step 6: Update database with collected waste statistics.
Step 7: If user disposed correctly → increase eco-points.
Step 8: Display status on dashboard.
Step 9: Repeat for next waste input.
